# Pulse AI Agent Conventions

## Framework

Google ADK (`google.adk.agents`) with Gemini models via FastAPI + uvicorn.

## Agent Types

| Type | Use |
|------|-----|
| `BaseAgent` | Custom routing logic (e.g., `DeterministicIntentRouterAgent`) |
| `LlmAgent` | LLM-powered agents with instructions + tools |
| `SequentialAgent` | Pipeline of sub-agents run in order |
| `ParallelAgent` | Sub-agents run concurrently |

## Root Architecture

```
DeterministicIntentRouterAgent (keyword routing)
├── data_query_pipeline (SequentialAgent)
│   ├── query_classifier_pipeline
│   ├── sql_generator_agent
│   └── sql_syntax_validator
└── conversational_agent
```

## Tool Pattern

```python
from google.adk.tools import FunctionTool

def my_tool(tool_context: ToolContext) -> dict:
    value = tool_context.state.get(STATE_KEYS.SOME_KEY)
    # ... deterministic logic ...
    tool_context.state[STATE_KEYS.RESULT] = result
    return {"status": "passed", "data": result}

my_function_tool = FunctionTool(my_tool)
```

## Registries

Dict-based configs in `registries/`: `METRICS_REGISTRY`, `TABLE_REGISTRY`, `FILTER_COLUMN_REGISTRY`. Each entry has `sql`, `unit`, `description`.

## Constants

- State keys: `constants/state_keys.py` → `STATE_KEYS.*`
- Error messages: `constants/error_messages.py` → `ERROR_MESSAGES.*`
- Enums: `constants/enums.py`

## SQL Safety

- SELECT-only queries (no DDL/DML)
- LIMIT enforcement on all generated SQL
- Time-range filters required
